description:
Somalia has declared a national drought emergency.
More than 4.5 million people face starvation, with nearly two million children malnourished.
Failed rains and extreme heat have devastated southern and central regions.
Aid agencies say the scale of need is overwhelming and resources are insufficient.
Displaced families are struggling with hunger and worsening conditions.
The crisis is accelerating as crops fail and livestock die.

Al Jazeera’s Catherine Soi reports from Mogadishu for Al Jazeera.
